---
import ElevationLayout from '../../layouts/ElevationLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../../components/elevation/Hero.astro';
import Section from '../../components/elevation/Section.astro';
import { getProductBySlug } from '../../lib/products/registry';
import { productJsonLd } from '../../lib/structured-data';

const product = getProductBySlug('trust-architecture-blueprint')!;
const jsonLd = productJsonLd(product, 'https://evoked.dev/products/trust-architecture-blueprint');
---

<ElevationLayout
  title="Trust Architecture Blueprint"
  description="Four pillars of agent trust: identity, memory, governance, and refusal rights. Build trust into the structure, not onto it. $49 PDF."
  structuredData={jsonLd}
>
  <Hero
    eyebrowParts={["Products", "Specification engineering"]}
    headline="What does your agent system actually trust?"
    metaphor={["Four pillars. One blueprint."]}
    sub="The foundation your agents are missing."
  />

  <Section marker="FIG · I" heading="Why this blueprint exists">
    <p class="lede">
      Most agent systems build capability first and trust later. Identity is an
      afterthought. Memory is whatever the framework gives you. Governance is
      "we'll add rules when something goes wrong." Refusal rights don't exist.
    </p>
    <p class="pd-body">
      This blueprint treats trust as architecture - four structural decisions that
      determine whether your system earns trust or just assumes it.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="FIG · II" heading="What you get">
    <div class="pd-features">
      <div class="pd-feature">
        <h3>Four-pillar framework</h3>
        <p>Identity, memory, governance, and refusal rights as interconnected architectural decisions. Not a checklist - a structural model.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-feature">
        <h3>Persona file templates</h3>
        <p>Define who your agent is - purpose, boundaries, voice, and standing positions. The difference between a prompt and an identity.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-feature">
        <h3>Session protocols</h3>
        <p>How agents open, close, and maintain continuity across sessions. Memory without protocol is just data accumulation.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-feature">
        <h3>Graduated trust stages</h3>
        <p>A model for increasing agent autonomy as trust is earned through demonstrated alignment - not granted by default.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="FIG · III" heading="The four pillars">
    <div class="pd-pillars">
      <div class="pd-pillar">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">1</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>Identity architecture</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">"Who is this agent - and how do you know?"</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-pillar">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">2</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>Memory architecture</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">"What does it remember, what does it forget, and who decides?"</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-pillar">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">3</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>Governance architecture</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">"Who sets the boundaries - and what happens when they're crossed?"</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-pillar">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">4</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>Refusal rights</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">"Can the agent say no - and will the system listen?"</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="FIG · IV" heading="Who this is for">
    <div class="pd-audience">
      <div class="pd-audience-card">
        <h3>Multi-agent teams</h3>
        <p>Building systems where agents interact with each other and with people. Trust architecture determines whether those interactions compound value or compound risk.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-audience-card">
        <h3>Solo developers</h3>
        <p>Designing your first agent system and want to build trust into the structure from the start. Retrofitting trust is always more expensive.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-audience-card">
        <h3>Engineering leads</h3>
        <p>Evaluating your existing agent architecture against a structured trust model. Surface the gaps before your users find them.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="FIG · V" heading="Buy the blueprint">
    <div class="pd-purchase">
      <div class="pd-price">$49</div>
      <p class="pd-purchase-lead">PDF download. Build trust into as many systems as you need.</p>
      <a
        href={product.stripePaymentLink}
        class="pd-buy-cta"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener"
      >Buy the Blueprint</a>
      <p class="pd-purchase-fineprint">
        Includes the four-pillar framework, persona file templates, session
        protocols, graduated trust stages, and quarterly review template.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="NOTA · BENE" heading="Go deeper" closing={true}>
    <p class="lede">
      The blueprint gives you the architecture. If you want to build out specific
      pillars, three doorways from here.
    </p>
    <div class="pd-upsell">
      <a href="/case-studies/labyrinth" class="pd-upsell-card">
        <h3>See it in practice</h3>
        <p>We analyzed a real defensive AI security platform through the four pillars. See what trust architecture looks like in the wild.</p>
        <span class="pd-upsell-link">Read the case study &rarr;</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/products/trust-architecture-complete" class="pd-upsell-card">
        <h3>The complete bundle</h3>
        <p>All four trust architecture products - Blueprint, Voice, Governance, and Restraint - for $149. Save $47.</p>
        <span class="pd-upsell-link">See the bundle &rarr;</span>
      </a>
      <a href="https://cal.com/cal.com-evoked/discovery-call" class="pd-upsell-card" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <h3>Discovery call</h3>
        <p>Free 30-minute call to discuss your trust architecture and figure out next steps.</p>
        <span class="pd-upsell-link">Schedule &rarr;</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </Section>
</ElevationLayout>

<style>
  /* ============================================================
     Product detail page template - J register chrome.

     Uses .pd-* class prefix so the entire pattern lifts cleanly
     to the other 14 product detail pages. Sections used:

       FIG  I  - value prop intro (lede + body)
       FIG  II - features grid (4 brass-bordered cards)
       FIG  III- pillars/domains list (numbered items)
       FIG  IV - audience cards (3 brass-bordered cards)
       FIG  V  - purchase card (brass-bordered, brass-tinted)
       NOTA BB - upsell grid (3 brass-bordered link cards)

     Pages that don't have all six sections can drop unused
     blocks; the others render identically.
     ============================================================*/

  .pd-body {
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 0.95rem + 0.3vw, 1.1rem);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--el-text-soft);
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0;
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  /* ---- FIG II: feature grid ---- */
  .pd-features {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
    gap: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 1vw, 1.5rem);
    margin-top: clamp(1.5rem, 1rem + 1.5vw, 2.5rem);
  }
  .pd-feature {
    padding: clamp(1.25rem, 1rem + 0.75vw, 1.75rem);
    border: 1px solid var(--el-rule);
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
  }
  .pd-feature:hover { border-color: var(--el-accent); }
  .pd-feature h3 {
    font-family: var(--el-display);
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 0.95rem + 0.3vw, 1.15rem);
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--el-text);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .pd-feature p {
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    font-size: clamp(0.95rem, 0.9rem + 0.2vw, 1.05rem);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--el-text-soft);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ---- FIG III: pillar list (numbered) ---- */
  .pd-pillars {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    margin-top: clamp(1.5rem, 1rem + 1.5vw, 2.5rem);
    border: 1px solid var(--el-rule);
  }
  .pd-pillar {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 1vw, 1.75rem);
    padding: clamp(1rem, 0.85rem + 0.6vw, 1.5rem) clamp(1.25rem, 1rem + 0.75vw, 1.75rem);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--el-rule);
  }
  .pd-pillar:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .pd-pillar-number {
    font-family: var(--el-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 1.25rem + 1.5vw, 2.25rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--el-accent);
    line-height: 0.9;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 2rem;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .pd-pillar-body { flex: 1; min-width: 0; }
  .pd-pillar-body h3 {
    font-family: var(--el-display);
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 0.95rem + 0.3vw, 1.15rem);
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--el-text);
    margin: 0 0 0.35rem;
  }
  .pd-pillar-question {
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(0.9rem, 0.85rem + 0.2vw, 1rem);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--el-text-quiet);
    margin: 0;
  }
  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .pd-pillar { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; gap: 0.5rem; }
    .pd-pillar-number { width: auto; text-align: left; }
  }

  /* ---- FIG IV: audience cards ---- */
  .pd-audience {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 1vw, 1.5rem);
    margin-top: clamp(1.5rem, 1rem + 1.5vw, 2.5rem);
  }
  .pd-audience-card {
    padding: clamp(1.25rem, 1rem + 0.75vw, 1.75rem);
    border: 1px solid var(--el-rule);
  }
  .pd-audience-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--el-display);
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 0.95rem + 0.3vw, 1.15rem);
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--el-text);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .pd-audience-card p {
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    font-size: clamp(0.95rem, 0.9rem + 0.2vw, 1.05rem);
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--el-text-soft);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ---- FIG V: purchase card ---- */
  .pd-purchase {
    max-width: 520px;
    margin: clamp(1.5rem, 1rem + 1.5vw, 2.5rem) auto 0;
    padding: clamp(1.75rem, 1.25rem + 1.5vw, 2.75rem);
    border: 2px solid var(--el-accent);
    background: color-mix(in oklab, var(--el-accent) 6%, transparent);
    text-align: center;
  }
  .pd-price {
    font-family: var(--el-display);
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 1.75rem + 2.5vw, 3.5rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--el-accent);
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .pd-purchase-lead {
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    font-size: clamp(0.95rem, 0.9rem + 0.25vw, 1.1rem);
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--el-text-soft);
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }
  .pd-buy-cta {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.85rem 2rem;
    background: var(--el-accent);
    color: var(--el-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--el-accent);
    font-family: var(--el-ui);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 13px;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background 0.2s ease, color 0.2s ease;
  }
  .pd-buy-cta:hover {
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--el-accent);
  }
  .pd-purchase-fineprint {
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    font-size: clamp(0.8rem, 0.75rem + 0.2vw, 0.9rem);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--el-text-quiet);
    margin: 1.5rem 0 0;
    max-width: 50ch;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  /* ---- NOTA BENE: upsell cards ---- */
  .pd-upsell {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
    gap: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 0.75vw, 1.5rem);
    margin-top: clamp(1.5rem, 1rem + 1.5vw, 2.5rem);
  }
  .pd-upsell-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    padding: clamp(1.25rem, 1rem + 0.75vw, 1.75rem);
    border: 1px solid var(--el-rule);
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
  }
  .pd-upsell-card:hover { border-color: var(--el-accent); }
  .pd-upsell-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--el-display);
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 0.95rem + 0.3vw, 1.15rem);
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--el-text);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .pd-upsell-card p {
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    font-size: clamp(0.9rem, 0.85rem + 0.2vw, 1rem);
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--el-text-soft);
    margin: 0;
    flex: 1;
  }
  .pd-upsell-link {
    font-family: var(--el-ui);
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--el-accent);
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
  }
</style>
